<concept id="concept_axv_vfm_mr">
 <title>Corpus Navigator </title>
 <conbody>
  <p>The "Corpus Navigator" tab is located on the left side of the "Text Corpus" work space. Here
   you can see the position of the text in the corpus, displayed hierarchically. You can navigate
   through the corpus by clicking the database objects or using the "up" and "down" arrow keys on
   your keyboard.</p>
  <p>Apart from the object title, the physical location of the database object is displayed in the
   square brackets. The number of elements it contains is shown in round brackets. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/corpus.png" id="image_plq_kjs_4r"/> marks all <xref
    href="oberflaeche_preferences.dita">activated</xref> corpora, for which you have the updater or
   reader role. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/corpus-disabled.png" id="image_pxc_mjs_4r"/> marks all
   other corpora.</p>
  <p>"Corpus Navigator" has two tabs: <image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/corpora.png"
    id="image_o21_2y3_zs"/> "Text Corpora" and <image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/bin.png"
    id="image_vqw_pjs_4r"/> "Bin". By default the tab "Text Corpora" is activated. In the "Bin" tab
   you can find your deleted texts and objects. Please note that generating the list of the objects
   in the "Bin" tab may take up to one minute the first time you click it after installing BTS.
   Thereafter the preview works faster. </p>
  <p>At the top of the "Corpus Navigator" window there are several buttons. Two of them, <image
    href="Images/icons/extra%20icons/minimize.png" id="image_j4m_cbb_qr"/> and <image
    href="Images/icons/extra%20icons/maximize.png" id="image_jyp_2bb_qr"/>, are also available in
   other windows and are therefore explained in the <xref href="oberflaeche_funktionen_e5.dita"
    >"Common features"</xref> section. </p>
  <p>"Corpus Navigator"-specific buttons are the following: </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/corpus-add.png" id="image_ksx_zjs_4r"/> "New Corpus":
   Click to create a new corpus. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/tcobject-add.png" id="image_szx_zjs_4r"/> "Add Text
   Corpus Object": Adds a "child"-object to the currently selected database object. You choose the
   active element by clicking it. It is called "BTSTC Object" until you rename it in the Passport
   Editor. NOTE: The physical location where the child element is saved is not the active corpus but
   your main working corpus you have choosen in the Preference Settings . </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/text-add.png" id="image_ahy_zjs_4r"/> "addNewText": Adds
   a "child" text to the selected corpus. It is called "BTS Text" until you rename it in the
   Passport Editor. NOTE: The physical location where the child element is saved is not the active
   corpus but your main working corpus you have choosen in the Preference Settings .</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/annotation-add.png" id="image_cpy_zjs_4r"/>
   "addAnnotation": Adds an annotation to the active object. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/comment-add.png" id="image_vm2_gbg_ys"/> "Add Comment":
   Adds a comment to the active object.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/obj16/delete.png" id="image_awy_zjs_4r"/> "Delete": Moves the
   selected element from the "Corpus Navigator" tab to the "Bin" tab. In the "Bin" you can either
   restore it or permanently delete it per right-click. </p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/search.png" id="image_ocz_zjs_4r"/> "Open Simple Search
   Dialog": Open a search dialog. </p>
  <p/>
  <p>Clicking <image href="Images/icons/extra%20icons/options_dreieck.png" id="image_zj3_d2g_ys"/>
   will display the drop-down menu with the following options:</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/corpus-add.png" id="image_g2q_ydg_ys"/> "Create New Text
   Corpus": see above.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/tcobject-add.png" id="image_t3d_xdg_ys"/> "Add TC
   Object": see above.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/text-add.png" id="image_px5_wdg_ys"/> "Add Text": see
   above.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/annotation-add.png" id="image_pzk_wdg_ys"/> "Add
   Annotation": see above.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/comment-add.png" id="image_kdb_wdg_ys"/> "Add Comment":
   see above.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/obj16/delete.png" id="image_d2r_vdg_ys"/> "Delete": see
   above.</p>
  <p>"Delete Permanently": Use this option to delete an item completely (it will not be moved to the
   bin).</p>
  <p>"Restore": Click to restore an item from the bin.</p>
  <p>"Move Object among Projects":</p>
  <p>"Open Conflict Dialog":</p>
  <p>"Present"</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/history.png" id="image_kn5_gjc_sr"/> "Open Revision
   History": see <xref href="oberflaeche_edit.dita">Menu bar -> Edit</xref>.</p>
  <p><image href="Images/icons/full/icon16/userrole.png" id="image_yjj_x3c_sr"/> "Edit
   Updaters/Readers": see <xref href="oberflaeche_edit.dita">Menu bar -> Edit</xref>.</p>
  <p>"Filter": filters the corpora according to the listed criteria. </p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
